<!-- FEATURES -->
<section id="features">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="kicker">Features</div>
      <h2 class="h2">Everything you need to ship dashboards faster</h2>
      <p class="sub">A focused toolset for developers building real Blazor interfaces — not toy demos.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="feature">
        <div class="icon">◉</div>
        <h3>Prompt-to-Dashboard</h3>
        <p>Describe the dashboard you need. Bilboard generates a fully structured BIL layout you can edit, export, or drop into your project.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <div class="icon">◧</div>
        <h3>Built on BIL Components</h3>
        <p>Every output uses native BIL primitives — charts, tables, cards, layouts — so it behaves like code your team would actually write.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <div class="icon">⟁</div>
        <h3>Agentic AI Workflow</h3>
        <p>Specialized agents plan, compose, and validate the dashboard structure step-by-step instead of dumping a single brittle response.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <div class="icon">⌬</div>
        <h3>Token-Efficient Output</h3>
        <p>A compact intermediate representation lets Bilboard produce dashboards using 2.8× fewer tokens than Claude in head-to-head tests.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <div class="icon">⟦⟧</div>
        <h3>Developer-Friendly Structure</h3>
        <p>Clean, readable Razor markup with predictable naming, typed bindings, and component boundaries that match your existing style.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <div class="icon">⇡</div>
        <h3>Rapid Blazor Prototyping</h3>
        <p>Iterate on layouts in seconds. Go from idea to a clickable dashboard prototype without writing the scaffolding by hand.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- EFFICIENCY -->
<section id="efficiency">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="kicker">Efficiency</div>
      <h2 class="h2">2.8× more token-efficient than Claude</h2>
      <p class="sub">We benchmarked dashboard generation tasks against Claude using identical prompts. Bilboard's agentic pipeline consistently produced equivalent dashboards using a fraction of the tokens.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="eff-grid">
      <div>
        <div class="big-stat">2.8×</div>
        <p class="big-stat-label">Fewer tokens to generate the same dashboard, measured across 50 representative Blazor dashboard prompts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="compare-card">
        <div class="vs-row">
          <div class="vs-label">Claude</div>
          <div class="vs-bar"><div class="claude"></div></div>
          <div class="vs-val">~14,200 tok</div>
        </div>
        <div class="vs-row">
          <div class="vs-label">Bilboard</div>
          <div class="vs-bar"><div class="bilboard"></div></div>
          <div class="vs-val">~5,070 tok</div>
        </div>
        <p class="note">Average tokens consumed per dashboard generation task. Lower is better.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
<section id="how">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="kicker">How it works</div>
      <h2 class="h2">Three steps from prompt to production</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">01</div>
        <h3>Enter your prompt</h3>
        <p>Describe the dashboard, the data shape, and any specific BIL components you want. Plain English works.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">02</div>
        <h3>AI generates the structure</h3>
        <p>Bilboard's agents plan the layout, pick the right BIL components, and assemble a coherent dashboard skeleton.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">03</div>
        <h3>Export or use directly</h3>
        <p>Copy the Razor output into your project, or continue iterating in Bilboard until the result is exactly right.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

