<!-- FAQ -->
<section id="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="kicker">FAQ</div>
      <h2 class="h2">Frequently asked questions</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <details open>
        <summary>What is Bilboard?</summary>
        <p>Bilboard is an agentic AI platform that turns natural-language prompts into production-ready Blazor dashboards built on top of BIL (Blazor Interface Library).</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Is it only for Blazor?</summary>
        <p>Yes — Bilboard is purpose-built for Blazor and outputs native BIL components. That focus is what enables higher quality and lower token usage than general-purpose models.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Does it use BIL components?</summary>
        <p>Every generated dashboard is composed entirely of BIL primitives, so the output looks and behaves like code your team would write by hand.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How is it different from Claude?</summary>
        <p>Claude is a general-purpose LLM. Bilboard is a specialized agentic pipeline tuned for Blazor dashboard generation, which is why it consistently uses 2.8× fewer tokens to produce equivalent results.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Who is it for?</summary>
        <p>Blazor developers, internal-tools teams, and AI builders who need to ship dashboards quickly without rewriting boilerplate every time.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can I customize the generated dashboard?</summary>
        <p>Absolutely. Output is clean Razor markup — edit it directly, iterate with follow-up prompts, or extend it with your own BIL components.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

